In [8]:
#Graphing daily new cases by state

graph_df = pd.DataFrame()
for region in df['state'].unique()[:]:
    region_df = df.copy()[df['state']==region]
    region_df.set_index("Date", inplace =True)
    region_df.sort_index(inplace=True)
    region_df[f'{region} New Cases by Day'] = region_df['positiveIncrease']
    
    if graph_df.empty: 
        graph_df = region_df[[f'{region} New Cases by Day']]
        
    else:
        graph_df = graph_df.join(region_df[f'{region} New Cases by Day'])
        
        %matplotlib inline
graph_df.plot(figsize=(18,18))

#Same graph, but this time with a 7 day moving average
graph_df = pd.DataFrame()
for region in df['state'].unique()[:]:
    region_df = df.copy()[df['state']==region]
    region_df.set_index("Date", inplace =True)
    region_df.sort_index(inplace=True)
    region_df[f'{region}_New Case 7 Day MA'] = region_df['positiveIncrease'].rolling(7).mean()
    
    if graph_df.empty: 
        graph_df = region_df[[f'{region}_New Case 7 Day MA']]
        
    else:
        graph_df = graph_df.join(region_df[f'{region}_New Case 7 Day MA'])
        
        %matplotlib inline
graph_df.plot(figsize=(18,18))

#Same graph, but this time with a 7 day moving average
graph_df = pd.DataFrame()
for region in df['state'].unique()[:]:
    region_df = df.copy()[df['state']==region]
    region_df.set_index("Date", inplace =True)
    region_df.sort_index(inplace=True)
    region_df[f'{region}_positive 7 day ma'] = region_df['positive'].rolling(1).mean()
    
    if graph_df.empty: 
        graph_df = region_df[[f'{region}_positive 7 day ma']]
        
    else:
        graph_df = graph_df.join(region_df[f'{region}_positive 7 day ma'])
        
        %matplotlib inline
graph_df.plot(figsize=(18,18))
